            <h1 class="h2 pb-3">Usage Guidelines</h1>
            <p>The following guidelines provide instructions on how to use the Not By AI badges.</p>
            <ul>
              <li class="pb-2">Linking the badge is strongly recommended as it allows your audience to learn more about the Not By AI mission. For assistance with linking the badge, please refer to <a href="/help/how-do-i-link-my-not-by-ai-badge.php" class="text-decoration-underline">How Do I Link My Not By AI Badge?</a>. </li>
              <li class="pb-2">Respect the clear space: Clear space is the surrounding area around the badge that should avoid any content. The minimum clear space is the x-height of the Not By AI typemark, as shown below.<br><img class="img-fluid my-3 ms-2" src="/img/not-by-ai-badge-x-height-brand-clearspace.svg" alt="X-height of the Not By AI badge using as clear space"></li>
              <li class="pb-2">Minimum Size: To ensure legibility, maintain a minimum display height of 42 px for screens with any resolution. However, use the @2x version of the image, which should have a height of 84 px, for 2x resolution screens to ensure clarity and sharpness.</li>
              <li class="pb-2">While the Not By AI badge is meant to be noticeable, the content creator is welcome to place the badge in a less visible area, such as a website footer, the plaque for your art, or the back of an album, to prevent the badge from visually competing with your content.</li>
              <li class="pb-2">Do not alter the badge: The badge should not be altered or modified in any way.</li>
            </ul>
